Psalm 83-12 <t>who said, <f>ⓩ</f>“Let us take possession for ourselves </t><t>of the pastures of God.” </t>
Psalm 83-13 <pb/><t>O my God, make them like <f>ⓐ</f>whirling dust, <f>[1]</f> </t><t>like <f>ⓑ</f>chaff before the wind.</t>
Psalm 83-14 <t>As <f>ⓒ</f>fire consumes the forest, </t><t>as the flame <f>ⓓ</f>sets the mountains ablaze,</t>
Psalm 83-15 <t>so may you pursue them <f>ⓔ</f>with your tempest </t><t>and terrify them with your hurricane!</t>
Psalm 83-16 <t><f>ⓕ</f> Fill their faces with shame, </t><t>that they may seek your name, O LORD.</t>
Psalm 83-17 <t>Let them be <f>ⓖ</f>put to shame and dismayed forever; </t><t>let them perish in disgrace,</t>
Psalm 83-18 <t>that they may <f>ⓗ</f>know that you alone, </t><t><f>ⓘ</f>whose name is the LORD, </t><t>are <f>ⓙ</f>the Most High over all the earth. </t>